    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0rm75di">
      <bpmn:text>documentation of the analysis tools, among others:
* designation/naming of the tools used with the corresponding versions
* definition and indication of the calculation of metrics such as TMB (tumor mutational burden), HRD, MSI
* specification of databases
* indication of the cut-offs (tolerance values) for the individual calculations</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_1abjmmj" sourceRef="Activity_05w6tvq" targetRef="TextAnnotation_0rm75di" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_1er2nm3">
      <bpmn:text>participants: pathologist, human genetics, haematology/ oncology specialist, tumour-specific disciplines (tumor entity expert)</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_0fbn0uq" sourceRef="Activity_1vtq62m" targetRef="TextAnnotation_1er2nm3" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_01o8n4o">
      <bpmn:text>Next-Generation Sequencing (NGS):
* DNA: Panel
* or WES, (WGS)
if necessary, additional diagnostics:
* RNA panel, transcriptome
* other optional methods
in case of abnormalities, validation by standard sequencing methods</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_1mxuqd3" sourceRef="Activity_010pmlt" targetRef="TextAnnotation_01o8n4o" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0nfd44x">
      <bpmn:text>presentation based on documented recommendation of a tumour entity or organ-specific tumour conference:
- Patients with advanced or rare cancer,
- who have progressed through guideline-based therapy,
- who clinically qualify for molecular-based therapy, and
- who agree in principle to a possible therapy based on
the molecular findings (see e.g. patient information).</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_1qba4nr" sourceRef="StartEvent_1" targetRef="TextAnnotation_0nfd44x" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_0ckkl82">
      <bpmn:text>participants: bioinformatician, molecular biology, pathologist, human genetics, haematology/ oncology specialist, tumour-specific disciplines (tumor entity expert)</bpmn:text>
    </bpmn:textAnnotation>
    <bpmn:association id="Association_0uxqf6y" sourceRef="Activity_1phtl9y" targetRef="TextAnnotation_0ckkl82" />
    <bpmn:textAnnotation id="TextAnnotation_116k17m">
      <bpmn:text>study participation (early phase), off-label therapy, no further therapy</bpmn:text>
